This position reports to Product Lead and interfaces with software developers and customers. bantu (which means ’to help’ in Malay is a social tech startup that supercharges Community Management &amp; Engagement for the social sector, to easily recruit, manage, &amp; retain volunteers, members &amp; event participants. bantu is committed to an employee-orientated, high performance culture that emphasises on creating social impact through good technology products.

Specific Responsibilities:
1. Plan and implement new designs
2. Communicate with customers to understand business goals
3. Deliver intuitive and user-centred solutions
4. Create prototypes for new product ideas
5. Conduct ongoing user research

Technical Skills and Competencies Trainee will learn during SGUnited Traineeship Programme:
1. Applications Integration
2. Business Needs Analysis
3. Change Management
4. Infrastructure Design
5. Database Administration
6. Network Administration and Maintenance
7. Software Configuration
8. Problem Management

Eligibility Criteria for SGUnitedTraineeships:
Singapore Citizen or Permanent Resident; anda.Graduated or graduating in calendar year 2019 or 2020 from ITEs, polytechnics, universities, or other educational institutions (e.g. private universities and overseas institutions); orb.Graduated earlier from above institutions and completed National Service in 2019 or 2020.